{"TopicId":201694,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mod to see flight data on main screen?","CreatedByName":"Rylant","CreatedById":211132,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-13T23:51:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rylant","CreatedById":211132,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-13T23:51:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all. Is there a current mod that will allow you to see flight data, particularly apoapsis and periapsis on the main screen? I don\u2019t\u00A0like fumbling back and forth between the main screen and the map screen as I try to achieve orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried to get Kerbal Engineer Redux to work as I understand that mod has that feature, but I couldn\u2019t get it to work. Is that because the mod hasn\u2019t been updated for the most recent version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Thanks,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Rylant\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-13T23:52:23Z\u0022 title=\u002204/13/2021 11:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 13, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Rylant\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-14T09:00:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/211132-rylant/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022211132\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/211132-rylant/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rylant\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0welcome to the Forums\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need the latest one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002232393\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5117887262\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/17833-130-kerbal-engineer-redux-1130-2017-05-28/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:196px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou also want to use the HUDS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E change the settings to be partless,\u00A0 and take off any career mode options so you always have access to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeace.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-14T09:10:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs a side note: don\u0060t use the \u0022Download from Curseforge\u0022 because it\u0060s an old version. Use the link in the first sentence to jrbudda\u0060s github. There you will find an up-to-date version which works in 1.11.x (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E 1.1.8.3).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rylant","CreatedById":211132,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-14T14:55:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you so much. I think the problem might have been that I didn\u2019t have partless enabled. Of course nobody has an engineer on the early flights so maybe that is why the hud was disabled. Now that I have enabled that function, it seems to be working. I feel like that should be vanilla and not need a mod.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Rylant\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-21T15:18:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see a mod that puts a semi-functional mini-map on your main view. I know putting it on a second monitor is close to being out of the question.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Caerfinon","CreatedById":207619,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-21T15:58:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223958274\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221619018288\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022102512\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Probus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, Probus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see a mod that puts a semi-functional mini-map on your main view. I know putting it on a second monitor is close to being out of the question\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScanSat has this ability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HA28jlN.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HA28jlN.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-21T17:05:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t realize that.\u00A0 Does it have any functionality (mainly just editing maneuver nodes)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-21T18:59:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso if it\u2019s just ap/pe info you want, the dialog at the bottom left (shows pitch by default) has a button (bottom of the 4 there,\u00A0looks like an orbit) now that changes the display to show this info.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Caerfinon","CreatedById":207619,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-22T11:02:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223958347\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221619024751\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022102512\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Probus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Probus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it have any functionality (mainly just editing maneuver nodes)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt pretty much just displays map information from ScanSat. You can overlay resources, slope, etc I primarily use it just to see where I am.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-22T12:48:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNavhud\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlight indicators\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteam gauges\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nare all mods to show a visual indication on screen of various infi\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flart","CreatedById":181486,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-01T10:36:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe stock game\u00A0has \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E on the flight screen since 1.7:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022pxam1aL.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002242.53\u0022 height=\u0022259\u0022 width=\u0022609\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/pxam1aL.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother mod, isn\u0027t mentioned there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022181486\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7302452158\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169611-110-speed-unit-annex-%E2%80%94-enhanced-navball-panel-contextually-2020-10-27/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}